Package: sysperf
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: lightweight Linux system-performance monitor (Performance tab)
 sysperf brings the information density of the Windows Task Manager Performance
 tab to the Linux desktop: CPU, memory, disk, network and GPU, each with a
 rolling 60-second graph and aggregate readouts, while staying small enough not
 to consume the resources it measures.
 .
 It is a single unprivileged process using honest Linux semantics (e.g. "In use"
 is MemTotal - MemAvailable, and slab counters are labelled as slab). GPU support
 uses NVML (loaded at runtime) and DRM fdinfo counters with graceful degradation
 across NVIDIA, Intel and AMD hardware. The Depends line is generated by
 dh_shlibdeps; Qt 6 is used under LGPLv3 via dynamic linking.
